Question: To find minimum, maximum element in an array
# initiazing user input
user_input=input("Enter the elements with spaces: ")

#splitting input values and storing in array
arr= user_input.split()

#Converting string values to int and sorting in order(Asc by default)
arr_elements= sorted(int(element) for element in arr)

#To print minimum value
print(f'Minimum Value is: {arr_elements[0]}')

#To print maximum value
print(f'Maximum value is: {arr_elements[-1]}')
